Tech Companies Data Analysis Report (Improved)
1. Objective

To analyze performance of global technology companies based on revenue, profit, and workforce, and identify efficiency patterns.

2. Data Cleaning
Removed symbols ($, commas) from revenue and profit columns
Converted financial data into numeric format
Cleaned employee data and converted to integer
Checked for missing and duplicate values
3. Key Analysis
Industry & Country Distribution
Majority of companies are concentrated in a few countries
Indicates geographic dominance in tech industry
Top Companies by Revenue & Profit
Top companies dominate total revenue and profit
However, high revenue does not always translate into high profit
Employees vs Revenue
Positive relationship exists
Some companies generate high revenue with fewer employees
👉 Indicates higher efficiency
Profit Margin Analysis
Profit margin calculated to evaluate efficiency
Smaller companies sometimes outperform larger ones
👉 Efficiency > size
4. Conclusion
Tech industry shows strong competition
Large companies dominate scale
Efficient companies outperform in profitability
Profit margin is a key indicator of performance
